<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-1408] Width of space character is calculated wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1408</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;PDFStreamEngine calculates width of space (line 357):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spaceWidthText = (font.getFontWidth( SPACE_BYTES, 0, 1 )*glyphSpaceToTextSpaceFactor);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In some cases the result is 0.&lt;br/&gt;
Problem is that getFontWidth requires code number of &quot; &quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there is &quot;ToUnicode&quot; mapping for that font that it is necessary to lookup CMap for code number and NOT to use 0x20 (space) as it is in souce code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
