                            <comment id="13451817" author="chupacabras" created="Mon, 10 Sep 2012 08:40:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached file contains font with ToUnicode mapping.&lt;br/&gt;
That results to wrong calculation of space width.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13451824" author="chupacabras" created="Mon, 10 Sep 2012 08:55:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the &quot;fast &amp;amp; ugly&quot; fix.&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s just to show what I mean so the &quot;pretty version&quot; of this fix is up to you &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actually I am not sure PDFStreamEngine.java is the best place to put this fix in. Maybe the better place would be PDSimpleFont.getFontWidth&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13475822" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 14 Oct 2012 11:35:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I adapted Juraj proposal as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;store the mapping for the space character within the CMap&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;implemented a new method PDFont/PDSimpleFont#getSpaceWidth which determines the width using the ToUnicode map if present, otherwise the old method is used&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the average font width is used as fall back value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I added all that stuff in revisions 1398055,1398056 and 1398057&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
